race.comment: MISS CHAMONIX (9) was only beaten 1.3L over 2020m at Doomben and then was only fair to the line at Eagle Farm back to this distance. This is much more suitable, and she finally draws an inside barrier. Has a small claim and deserves to break through. IRISH ACCOLADE (12) switched yards last time and disappointed a tad over a mile at the Sunshine Coast. He'd been racing in stronger company in NSW, and the longer journey will suit. Has had plenty of chances, but this isn't hard, and he should get his chance. PELLINOR (8) tries hard and can go better back in trip. Maps well and should be around the mark. JAMCART (6) has switched from the Munce yard and will likely appreciate the longer journey. JUST BEAUTY (1) has more upside than most of these but this may be a stretch at this stage.
